  Ari, I looked at DAoC, and I just didn't see enough to interest me. RvR doesn't seem to have the type of balance I am looking for, nor much point to it. If I go to another &quot;RPG&quot;, I want the game to have more to do than some tradeskills and killing. It's probably low priority stuff to every game programmer out there, but I want a world with more life to it, where NPCs carry on regardless of the number of PCs playing, and react to PC actions. I'd like to be able to sit down at a table and play a game of poker or strip blackjack. I also don't want a world where you have humans with so much more power than beginners.<br>
<br>
  I've kept a little eye on DAoC, keeping in mind the huge biases on message boards, remembering Flame Vault while I was enjoying EQ. I just don't see enough to interest me besides the fact that it's different looking with different classes. Also, considering how lax I am on my EQ equipment, I'd really hate to be buying / stealing new clothes all the time.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucarathosollathir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Carathos Ollathir</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalRainbow.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1393<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/26/02 10:24:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3211.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Price Increase</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> While 2 years seems like a long time to get &quot;locked in&quot;, many of us have already been playing that long.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Yeah, the game might still be here then, but who knows where you'll be in two years?  You can have any number of drastic life changes in that time period.  You can got off to college, move to another city, get married, start a family, lose your job, get thrown in prison for a crime you didn't commit (LIES!), and a few morbid things that I'll leave out.  I wouldn't commit to something that long without building up some sort of equity <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
